Visual Settings for Dashboard Chart Components

Choose the type of chart that fits the data you are sharing, then apply the visual settings that will communicate the data most effectively.

Formatting Settings for various dashboard components:

* Horizontal bar and vertical column charts: set scale and sorting to compare values.
* Funnel chart: use color to show status through stages.
* Scatter chart: display one or two groups of report data plus summaries.
* Gauge component: set breakpoints and colors to track current value.
* Line chart: use sorting and scale to show data over time.
* Metric component: use color to help users make sense of the data.
* Pie chart: configure and label divisions to show relative shares.
* Table component: use color and scale to interpret report data.
